      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "factorAcceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of simulation setup and boundary condition specification completed.",
      "rationale": "A qualitative assessment of use-error risk was conducted through structured peer review by a senior CFD engineer not involved in the original simulation setup. The reviewer examined mesh topology, boundary condition assignments, turbulence model selection (SST k-omega), and post-processing scripts for the hemolysis power-law model. No critical errors were identified. Minor documentation gaps in the impeller rotation reference-frame specification were corrected prior to final submission. The team concluded that the risk of consequential use error was low given the structured review process, the use of a validated simulation template, and the cross-check of results against an independent in-house Lattice Boltzmann code at a single operating point. This qualitative determination was judged sufficient for MRL 2 without formal grading against the ASME V&V 40 level scale."
